New Records: Travis Head set a new Australian record for the fastest T20I half-century against England, scoring it in 19 balls
Key Match Events: Travis Head scored 59 off 23 balls, Adam Zampa took 2-20 as Australia bowled England out for 151
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the first T20 match of the series between Australia and England
Others: Mitch Marsh hailed the performance of Travis Head, Adam Zampa, and Josh Hazlewood as key to Australia's victory
